hough multimodality is not uncommon and can significantly broaden the\nposteriors. The effective inspiral spin is best measured for neutron star black\nhole mergers, for which the uncertainties can be as low as $\\sim0.08$ ($\\sim\n0.2$) at SNR 12 (8). The uncertainty is higher for systems with comparable\ncomponent masses or lack of spin precession.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 23 Oct 2018 18:27:19 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 25 Oct 2018 00:20:05 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 21 Dec 2018 22:30:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-01-03"}
