{"id":"1810.10201","submitter":"Andrey Panov","authors":"Andrey V. Panov","title":"Giant enhancement and sign inversion of optical Kerr nonlinearity in\n  random high index nanocomposites near Mie resonances","comments":"8 pages, 7 figures, 2 tables","journal-ref":"Ann. Phys. (Berlin), 532, 1900574 (2020)","doi":"10.1002/andp.201900574","report-no":null,"categories":"physics.optics","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  High index dielectric nanoantennas excited at Mie-type resonances have\nexhibited enormous enhancement of optical nonlinearity. Such nanostructures\nhave been actively studied by researchers in the last years. The present work\nprovides the first numerical analysis study of the optical Kerr effect of\nnanocomposites consisting of high refractive index (GaP) spheres at the\nwavelength of 532~nm. This is done by means of three-dimensional\nfinite-difference time-domain (FDTD) simulations. The effective nonlinear\nrefractive index of $0.8$~$\\mu$m thick nanocomposites and metasurfaces is\nevaluated. It is shown that the optical Kerr nonlinearity of the nanocomposites\nrises by orders in proximity to Mie resonances and may exceed the second-order\nrefractive index of the bulk material. It is revealed that the sign of the\neffective optical Kerr coefficient is inverted near the Mie resonances. This\neffect may be of interest in developing nonlinear optical metadevices.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 24 Oct 2018 06:09:13 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 14 Mar 2019 02:03:59 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 29 Feb 2020 17:08:53 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 9 Jul 2020 13:56:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-10"}
