ain model together with ab initio rate data will enable more accu-\nrate modeling nonequilibrium phenomena, such as vibrationally-favored\ndissociation, an effect that is not well-captured by the conventional models\nprevalent in DSMC (i.e. Larsen-Borgnakke and Total Collision Energy).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 24 Oct 2018 15:22:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-20"}
